The feeding of an obese child: does not take breakfast and takes cold cuts for dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have problems overweight, 9% of schoolchildren will weigh above the average and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle.
This again shows how important is the environment in which the human being evolves and the models that surround him.
On the tables of obese children, for example, 50% cold cuts is found more often than in families of children with normal weight.
19% of the obese had fries at dinner according to the survey conducted with an awareness-raising action "Obesity is not a coincidence"
In the families of the big little ones the sport is also not a habit, which is now the case of most of today's schoolchildren - only 15% responded that at least once a week parents find time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and participated in 900 pupils from the primary schools in the Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of "Obesity is not a coincidence", an action supported by the General Health Insurance and the company Unilever.
Since the beginning, more than 12000 students from sixth to third have enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of overweight, even obese, children is the absence, of a proper diet and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half of the children surveyed indicate, for example, eating 5 times a day breakfast-in case - lunch - snack- dinner, which is a basic principle of good nutrition," says one of the results of the survey.
Without breakfast and cold cuts at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that to have a healthy development it takes some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of students’ families eat at the same time.
In most families each has breakfast alone.
And the worst that has been raised is that a tenth of the population does not eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in the families of obese children, unhealthy fries are more often consumed.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drinks sugary drinks every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children surveyed do sports regularly but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare your food
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own diets from opportunities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15 are far from the ideal in terms of healthy eating."
Among their favorite dishes are a lot of cakes, meats and sweets.
"The most alarming is a great preference for sweet lemonades," the survey results said.
For lunch it was the pasta that took the first place right in front of the white meat.
The children did not want starchy food at all and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Heading to Health
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the moment they receive the ad hoc information.
"During a check of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness session "Obesity is not a coincidence", a determined willingness to move towards a healthy diet was attended," the results of the survey said.
The most striking was, for example, with regard to sweet lemonades because children began to give preference to drinking water.
Children most often checked on the questionnaire white meat and fish as their main course and would reduce sweet dishes and "knedliky" (Czech speciality of bread flour or potato dumplings).
