The need for speed The Run is fought across America.
Revision
Originally a trouble-free race is transformed because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who don't care about it on a routine morning commute to work.
This fulfills everyone’s ambition to a certain extent, but it’s useless if no one wants to do something more.
The new subtitled part The Run produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed race series and release some kind of game from playable games that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how will be the added passages during which the main hero comes out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole is pulling down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of incomprehensible laziness on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught up in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to settle them begins to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to get first to New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
This results in each race taking place on another route and the stages planned in different environments that stand out quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also quite pretty even if the graphic technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
Finally, it is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are in addition from time to time embellished with an atypical element.
For example in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Next to this the different races are well arranged one behind the other.
There are only a few but that is enough.
There are moments you strive to surpass the number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classic duel with the timer) and then still awaits you another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and who try to make the situation hard.
The novelty is the off-car crossings.
It’s more of an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help them by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What’s surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
To the result it is good as this because this element is not likely to hinder and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means that there is nothing extraordinary right now, but we cannot say that it is negative.
As for the realistic simulation you will have to go elsewhere.
But although one can find better in competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is okay.
The problems begin to appear after some time.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not yet at the point.
We do not expect from this game a complicated deformation and collisions, but when you do not have, in a collision with any object, any idea of how your car behaves, so it is not completely good.
During the tight overtaking you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car goes off in crazy aerobatics.
Or else is in crumbs.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done so that when you have broken your face or you have come out in the set the game brings you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to start the game from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go the way it should, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes the restarts do not help and it is necessary to find the solution by remembering from memory the piece of route in question.
The great catch of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that must be passed in a certain way otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise you encounter on a given place civil vehicles always in the same configuration that you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds early or one minute late.
What makes things angry are the situations when you see the opponent easily passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you, you either have to put yourself aside and conturn them or brake.
It's equal if you go to the front of him because it's "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation he always arrives very close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about the time, and you still have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This annoys the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a good number of times.
It is understandable that the purpose of this game is to do something exciting and full of adredaline, but it is clear that you are getting bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and the places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it's equal if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is the change of car during the races.
You have to pay attention to the gas pumps on the routes because you can change cars there however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American displacements for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic attire on very technical driving for example on lace roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places you know from the adventure, goes very well with the main diet of history.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of conductor, different objects start to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog feature which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and gives you other functions in the community.
One of the hardest shots to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the darkness on the lanes (it looks like).
Your speedometer shows you between 150 and 200 km/hour (a priori) and behind you arrives a subway train that sends you the car directly to scrap metal.
At the editor we had a discussion for a few days to know if someone really thought about when creating this game or if the authors really think we are fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally nice and in some cases really great.
What bothers is that in more extreme situations, imagery does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This is mostly about accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is of your choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the youngest audience a new sound track was created in the style "I mix everything", but we can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Need for Speed: The Run is really confusing.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best production of NFS in recent years.
But this game gives the impression of not being finished.
The fun is really good but prepare yourself for the faults to hit you in the eyes with the strength of an airfield reflector.
Velvet Students in concert with Charles University choirs
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival, 20 choirs of higher schools and secondary classes occur.
The highlight of the festival consists of two concerts held on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of high schools and secondary classes which takes place with free entry on November 17 from 14 hours on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Velvet students" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools and that of Charles University take place.
The objective of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Day of Students and to recall the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Chewers in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from November 16 to 20 in Prague and Pardubice.
The program offers in addition to high-level concerts, msical meetings, a student happening and other activities.
Interested parties will find all the information on the festival's webpages www.festaacademica.cz.
