It will be recalled that Michoacán did not approve its Political Constitution or its State Electoral Code or its Law of Electoral Justice, at the same time as the State Congress approved the reforms shortly before the end of the legal period for this electoral trial to enter into force and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel omitted his publication within the time limits provided for by the Law of the Official Gazette of the State.
On the same November 9, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) resolved the constitutional controversy promoted by the local Legislative Power and called the state’s proxy’s proxy vote for constitutional reforms “invalid and illegal” because it has no right to “sanction or challenge them.”
Interviewed on the possibility of the "vote by vote", María de los Ángeles Llanderal said that thanks to the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the IEM General Council it will be possible to carry out the biased and total counts of the votes by the local electoral body.
Thus, the partial counting of votes, of one or more electoral packets, it may be that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there are no ballot minutes and counting in the record of the ballot block is not found in the president of the ballot room; or there are obvious errors or alterations of the minutes.
In addition, the total count of votes received in all ballot boxes in the election may be made where there is an indication that the difference between the assumed candidate winning the respective election and the one who obtained the second place in the election is equal to or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express petition from the representative of the party and/or coalition who presented the second of the candidates.
The total counting of the vote can also be realized if at the end of the joint count it results that the difference between the supposed candidate winner and that of the second place is equal to or less than a percentage point, provided that there is the express petition of the representative of the political party from which the candidate has emerged second, in which case the electoral packets which have been the subject of the partial count will be excluded.
It should be mentioned that this is the situation of Morelia's election, where according to the PREP, the difference between the first and second place is only 0.16 percent, even without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total minutes.
