Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A Cali typist went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano."
The work of these officials is crucial.
The past November 4 a Cita ITC dactyloscopist has made history as the person who confirmed the identity of the supreme leader of the FARC: "Alfonso Cano", confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven typists who work in the local offices of the CTI, this week it was the "availability" tour of Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working for 21 years in the field of judicial investigation.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Chocó, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to get to the place where the corpses that were to be identified were located.
The year 2000 he was transferred to the capital of Valle and after having taken adequate courses, he specialized in typing, which is the study of the skin of friction, that is to say the palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar had been warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected was that of the man who ran the oldest guerrilla in the world, therefore he was asked to take the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the place of the corpse, he did not recognize him by his physical appearance, because it was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a peasant from the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But the prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a sampler and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the card.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the official who confirmed to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, it was the supreme leader of the FARC.
In search of the fingerprint
For a Typediologist from Sijín de Cali the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos gave to Eliazar González, in a press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
Many people do not know our work.
Typing is an exact science, without margin of error, that can be crucial in solving crimes.
Apart from identifying the corpses, the typists support the investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of the captured.
When captured, many offenders present false identity cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and search for them in the database.
The researcher said that in one case of theft he had to remove a part of a wall from a house, because in this place the thief had pressed his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
“The walls are difficult because they are not adequate areas to make a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to get the fingerprint with the whole hand and identify the offender who had participated in different thefts,” he recalls.
Prints can also rule out or confirm suspects in homicide cases.
Recently we found a dead man, with bottles of drink around him.
For the purposes of the investigation, it was determined that a parent may be a suspect of the crime and indeed a fingerprint on the bottle coincided.
Even if it doesn't guarantee that he's the murderer, it puts him at the scene of the crime.
A CTI typist explained that "the fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents" are extracted.
When they appear, a sampler or a band is used to remove them.
Subsequently, fingerprints are sent to Asif, the database of declinquents, or the National Civil Registry.
“The problem is that there are still a lot of undocumented Colombians,” the CTI expert said.
He explained that not everything is how one shows in the television program CSI.
Since everything that shines is not gold, everything that one touches does not necessarily become an imprint.
However, it can be used, if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
