A white-seing to the European absolute monarch or a jump joined in the void of nationalist retreat: what a choice for the citizen!
No, we do not want cleaves but an exercise, common, by right, serene and continuous, of choice and democracy, this time at European level.
There are no crises in Greece, Italy, Spain, Portugal - we can no longer stop the enumeration - because there is only one crisis, and it is in Europe.
It is the whole of Europe that bends to the dictates of the markets and rating agencies, which suffers from its powerlessness and its lack of solidarity.
It is the whole of Europe that is humiliated on the international stage.
We are concerned about the transfer of sovereignty to Europe - but it is the whole of Europe that is slowly losing its sovereignty, and with it each of its nations.
The urgency is to restore popular sovereignty to the steering of the European project.
Because it is together that Europeans will be able to reduce the burden of their debts, free themselves from the markets and prepare for the future by investing.
The end of the crisis will involve decisions at European level that cannot be taken without total democratic legitimacy, except of course to lead us to disaster.
After having long fought this proposal of the Socialists and Jacques Delors, everyone is now calling for the European economic government.
Be.
But thinking about it without a stronger political and democratic integration, and experienced as such by the citizens, would be a new madness and a new impasse.
We must take a new stage in European integration.
To make the Republic in France, it was necessary to "make" Republicans.
The revolution in the interests could not suffice.
This lesson is still valid.
We need to build a more economically integrated Europe.
This can only be achieved by building a more politically democratic Europe, a genuine European popular sovereignty.
To make Europe, let's make Europeans.
